cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR 

This paper is about face hallucination, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The method proposed in the paper involves the use of CNNs for generating facial components, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also involves the synthesis of fine-grained facial structures, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG and cs.AI. The other two sub-categories are less likely but still relevant to the paper's content.
